leted **Job 4: 回滚和恢复** (Rollback and Recovery) for the git_integration module. Here's what was accomplished:\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n**Created `internal/git/rollback.go`** with the following components:\n\n1. **ResetToCommit(hash)** - Performs hard reset to a specific commit hash with safety checks\n2. **ResetToVersion(version)** - Resets to a specific version tag with validation\n3. **GetDiff(fromCommit, toCommit)** - Returns structured diff information between commits\n4. **GetFileHistory(filePath)** - Retrieves complete commit history for a file\n5. **Safety Checks**:\n   - `checkUncommittedChanges()` - Prevents reset if there are uncommitted changes\n   - `commitExists()` - Validates commit hash before reset\n   - `ValidateCommit()` - Converts short hashes to full hashes\n\n6. **Helper Functions**:\n   - `HasUncommittedChanges()` - Checks for uncommitted changes\n   - `GetCurrentCommitHash()` - Gets current HEAD commit\n   - `ValidateCommit()` - Validates and normalizes commit hashes\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n**Created `internal/git/rollback_test.go`** with 10+ comprehensive tests:\n- ✅ TestResetToCommit - Tests commit reset functionality\n- ✅ TestResetToCommitInvalid - Tests error handling\n- ✅ TestResetToVersion - Tests version-based reset\n- ✅ TestResetToVersionInvalid - Tests error handling\n- ✅ TestGetDiff - Tests diff generation\n- ✅ TestGetDiffInvalid - Tests error handling\n- ✅ TestGetFileHistory - Tests file history retrieval\n- ✅ TestGetFileHistoryInvalid - Tests error handling\n- ✅ TestHasUncommittedChanges - Tests change detection\n- ✅ TestGetCurrentCommitHash - Tests hash retrieval\n- ✅ TestValidateCommit - Tests hash validation\n\n**Coverage: 83.2%** (exceeds 80% requirement)\n\n### Validation Results\n\nAll validators passed:\n- ✅ ResetToCommit() correctly rolls back to specified commits\n- ✅ ResetToVersion() correctly rolls back to version tags\n- ✅ GetDiff() correctly displays differences between commits\n- ✅ GetFileHistory() correctly re